From 1a4a96a8f08b5e30fbf94160b12da7a4f7a4ce08 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: walferlab <walferlab@gmail.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Jul 2026 06:21:14 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Fix random logouts, empty dashboard products, missing
 onboarding gate, and broken seller stats

- proxy.ts / SupabaseServer.ts: migrate deprecated get/set/remove cookie
  methods to getAll/setAll (required by @supabase/ssr 0.12.x). The old
  API doesn't reliably sync refreshed session cookies back to the
  browser, causing random logouts on navigation.
- dashboard/page.tsx: RecentProducts queried sellers.user_id, a column
  that doesn't exist (sellers.id IS the auth user id). Also wired real
  values into TotalProductsCard/TotalSalesCard/TotalViewsCard/
  Last30DaysCard, which were previously rendered with no data at all.
- dashboard/products/page.tsx: surface query errors instead of
  silently falling into the empty state.
- proxy.ts: gate /dashboard behind onboarding completion so new
  sellers land on /dashboard/onboarding instead of skipping it.
- DB: seller_metrics materialized view had zero grants (unreadable by
  any client role) and had never been refreshed since creation
  (always empty). Renamed it to seller_metrics_mv, wrapped it in a
  security_invoker view (seller_metrics) scoped to auth.uid() so
  sellers can only see their own row, granted SELECT to authenticated,
  did the required initial refresh, and added a trigger to refresh on
  product changes as well as sales.
